  "market_context": "Strong uptrend on EURUSD 15m; recent impulsive move created equal lows acting as support. Below those lows, a Fair Value Gap (FVG) was identified as a strong demand zone. The market swept the equal lows to trigger retail stop losses before reversing upward into the FVG.",
  "key_observation": "Price broke below equal lows to sweep sell-side liquidity, then reversed sharply into a pre-identified FVG zone—confirming a high-probability long setup aligned with the dominant bullish trend.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a strong uptrend on EURUSD 15m with a recent impulsive move forming equal lows (swing lows at same price level).",
    "Step 2: Recognized that below the equal lows lay a concentration of sell-side liquidity (retail stop losses), making it a likely target for a liquidity sweep.",
    "Step 3: Noted the presence of a Fair Value Gap (FVG) just below the equal lows, serving as a strong demand zone and optimal entry area after liquidity is swept.",
    "Step 4: Observed price breaking below the equal lows (invalidating short-term structure temporarily), confirming a liquidity sweep of sell-side orders.",
    "Step 5: Watched price reverse sharply and pull back into the FVG zone, where a long entry was taken with stop loss below the FVG, targeting buy-side liquidity above."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade executed at the FVG zone after liquidity sweep; price rallied toward buy-side liquidity as expected.",
  "lessons": "A break below equal lows in an uptrend may not signal reversal but rather a liquidity grab; always assess whether a demand zone (e.g., FVG) lies beneath—and enter only after the sweep completes and price re-enters the imbalance zone.",
